    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-07-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="436"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Governor <persName
                            type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-07-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 25, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Italian chargé reports that the grand jury of Madison Parish has declared its
                    inability to discover the persons who lynched the Italians at Tallulah. He
                    desires to be informed if further efforts will be made to discover and punish
                    the lynchers. It is my duty to remind your excellency that the treaty of the
                    United States with Italy accords to Italian subjects the most constant
                    protection and security for their persons and property, and I have assured the
                    Italian Government that all legal steps will be taken in the interests of
                    justice.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
